################################################################################
# Word order
################################################################################

# Abui does not have ditransitive verbs.

# Transitive verbs

#1 Grammatical (SOV)
Source: {a:129}
Vetted: {t}
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {word order}
Simon nala nee
Simon what eat
'Simon eats something.'

#2 Ungrammatical (SVO)
Source: {c}
Vetted: {f}
Judgment: u
Phenomena: {word order}
Simon nee nala
Simon eat what
'Simon eats something.'

#3 Ungrammatical (OSV)
Source: {c}
Vetted: {f}
Judgment: u
Phenomena: {word order}
nala Simon nee
what Simon eat
'Simon eats something.'

#4 Ungrammatical (OVS)
Source: {c}
Vetted: {f}
Judgment: u
Phenomena: {word order}
nala nee Simon
what eat Simon
'Simon eats something.'

#5 Ungrammatical (VSO)
Source: {c}
Vetted: {f}
Judgment: u
Phenomena: {word order}
nee Simon nala
what Simon eat
'Simon eats something.'

#6 Ungrammatical (VOS)
Source: {c}
Vetted: {f}
Judgment: u
Phenomena: {word order}
nee nala Simon
what eat Simon
'Simon eats something.'

# Intransitive verbs

#7 Grammatical (SV)
Source: {c}
Vetted: {f}
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {word order}
Simon taa
Simon sleep
'Simon is sleeping.'

#8 Ungrammatical (VS)
Source: {c}
Vetted: {f}
Judgment: u
Phenomena: {word order}
taa Simon
sleep Simon
'Simon is sleeping.'

################################################################################
# Pronouns
################################################################################

#7 Grammatical (first-person singular)
Source: {a:200}
Vetted: {t}
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {number, pn}
na taa
1SG sleep.CNT
'I am lying [in bed]/sleeping.'

#8 Grammatical (first-person plural exclusive)
Source: {c}
Vetted: {f}
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {number, pn}
ni taa
1PL.E sleep.CNT
'We (except you) are lying [in bed]/sleeping.'

#9 Grammatical (first-person plural inclusive)
Source: {c}
Vetted: {f}
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {number, pn}
pi taa
1PL.I sleep.CNT
'We (including you) are lying [in bed]/sleeping.'

#10 Grammatical (second-person singular)
Source: {c}
Vetted: {f}
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {number, pn}
a taa
2SG sleep.CNT
'You are lying [in bed]/sleeping.'

#11 Grammatical (second-person plural)
Source: {c}
Vetted: {f}
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {number, pn}
ri taa
2PL sleep.CNT
'Y'all are lying [in bed]/sleeping.'

#12 Grammatical (third-person)
Source: {c}
Vetted: {f}
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {number, pn}
di taa
3 sleep.CNT
'He/she/it/they are lying [in bed]/sleeping.'

################################################################################
# Case
################################################################################

# Abui has no case inflections of NPs.

